@{b}MAX()@{ub}

Usage:@{b}MAX(number,number[,number,...])@{ub}

Returns the maximum of the supplied arguments, all of which must be numeric. At
least two parameters must be supplied.

Example:
@{fg shine}
        say max(2.1, 3, -1)             ==>3
@{fg text}
